                <title>Settings.saveSetting()</title>
                <paragraph><literal>app.settings.saveSetting(sectionName, keyName, value[, prefType])</literal></paragraph>
                <paragraph><strong>Description</strong></paragraph>
                <paragraph>Saves a value for a script settings item.</paragraph>
                <warning>
                    <paragraph>If the value is greater than 1999 bytes, <literal>saveSetting</literal> that item will throw an error (seen in AE 15.0.1)</paragraph>
                </warning>
                <paragraph><strong>Parameters</strong></paragraph>
                <table>
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colwidth="15"></colspec>
                        <colspec colwidth="62"></colspec>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph><literal>sectionName</literal></paragraph>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph>A string containing the name of a settings section.</paragraph>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph><literal>keyName</literal></paragraph>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph>A string containing the key name of the setting item.</paragraph>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph><literal>value</literal></paragraph>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph>A string containing the new value.</paragraph>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph><literal>prefType</literal></paragraph>
                                </entry>
                                <entry>
                                    <paragraph>Optional, an enum indicating which preference file to use.</paragraph>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
                <paragraph><strong>Returns</strong></paragraph>
                <paragraph>Nothing.</paragraph>
                <paragraph><strong>Example</strong></paragraph>
                <paragraph>If you want to save a setting called “trimPrecomps” for a script named “Precomp Cropper”, you could save that setting via</paragraph>
                <literal_block classes="code javascript" force_highlighting="False" language="javascript" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve"><inline classes="keyword declaration">var</inline> <inline classes="name other">trimPrecompsSetting</inline> <inline classes="operator">=</inline> <inline classes="keyword constant">true</inline><inline classes="punctuation">;</inline>
<inline classes="name other">app</inline><inline classes="punctuation">.</inline><inline classes="name other">settings</inline><inline classes="punctuation">.</inline><inline classes="name other">saveSetting</inline><inline classes="punctuation">(</inline><inline classes="literal string double">"Precomp Cropper"</inline><inline classes="punctuation">,</inline> <inline classes="literal string double">"trimPrecomps"</inline><inline classes="punctuation">,</inline> <inline classes="name other">trimPrecompsSetting</inline><inline classes="punctuation">);</inline></literal_block>
                <paragraph>Note that the setting will be saved as a string. You’ll want to parse it into a bool later, if needed.</paragraph>
